1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:50,000
(Watch on www.kisskh.li Support Admin)

2
00:00:56,682 --> 00:01:00,978
MAD CONCRETE DREAMS

3
00:01:04,022 --> 00:01:06,733
9 YEARS AGO

4
00:01:07,693 --> 00:01:09,319
I'm not a fan of shamanism.

5
00:01:10,237 --> 00:01:12,114
Can't you go in on your own?

6
00:01:12,197 --> 00:01:13,407
Seon.

7
00:01:13,490 --> 00:01:16,618
Anyone successful in Korea
consults a fortune-teller.

8
00:01:16,994 --> 00:01:19,830
My mom trusts Master Park
more than her lawyer.

9
00:01:20,581 --> 00:01:22,541
She credits her for making her rich.

10
00:01:22,874 --> 00:01:24,167
- "Rich?"
- Yes.

11
00:01:24,251 --> 00:01:27,254
So take the plunge and come with me.

12
00:01:27,629 --> 00:01:30,132
Who knows?
We might get some awesome news.

13
00:01:30,549 --> 00:01:32,134
I still don't like it.

14
00:01:32,217 --> 00:01:34,219
- It's a waste of money, too.
- What money?

15
00:01:34,303 --> 00:01:36,597
You don't have to pay
if you're with me.

16
00:01:36,680 --> 00:01:39,349
I always came here with my mom.

17
00:01:39,433 --> 00:01:42,644
It's my first time coming on my own,
and it's a bit scary.

18
00:01:43,437 --> 00:01:45,564
You're the only one I can ask.

19
00:01:47,107 --> 00:01:48,108
Okay, then.

20
00:01:48,900 --> 00:01:51,820
CELESTIAL READER MASTER PARK

21
00:01:54,406 --> 00:01:55,616
How do you know each other?

22
00:01:56,491 --> 00:01:58,201
She's a good friend. Why?

23
00:01:59,661 --> 00:02:01,288
I see concern in your Four Pillars.

24
00:02:03,040 --> 00:02:04,916
Your household will become dark

25
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:06,126
as if it were struck by lightning.

26
00:02:08,003 --> 00:02:10,297
What does that mean?

27
00:02:10,672 --> 00:02:13,175
Why did you come back
when you won't listen to me?

28
00:02:13,675 --> 00:02:16,345
I told you not to marry that fool.

29
00:02:17,262 --> 00:02:19,264
You said there was a way out.

30
00:02:19,348 --> 00:02:20,849
We already tied the knot.

31
00:02:21,391 --> 00:02:23,268
Your only way out

32
00:02:23,602 --> 00:02:24,811
is to have a child.

33
00:02:25,145 --> 00:02:26,980
But that's easier said than done.

34
00:02:27,522 --> 00:02:29,274
Your flame is already so weak.

35
00:02:29,358 --> 00:02:31,485
A tiny wisp of air could blow it out.

36
00:02:32,152 --> 00:02:33,236
What's that supposed to mean?

37
00:02:33,737 --> 00:02:35,781
Quit saying stuff I can't understand.

38
00:02:35,864 --> 00:02:37,991
Tell me what to do.
Write me a paper talisman.

39
00:02:38,450 --> 00:02:40,369
Not even the great Madam Jeon

40
00:02:40,452 --> 00:02:42,287
can talk her daughter
out of anything.

41
00:02:42,371 --> 00:02:44,581
What more could I say to you?

42
00:02:44,665 --> 00:02:47,084
You only remember what you like.

43
00:02:47,167 --> 00:02:49,169
You can't talk to me like that.

44
00:02:49,252 --> 00:02:50,879
I've had enough of this.

45
00:02:50,962 --> 00:02:52,839
How dare you take that tone with me?

46
00:02:52,923 --> 00:02:53,924
- I...
- Yi-gyeong.

47
00:02:55,217 --> 00:02:57,552
You heard the way she talked.

48
00:02:58,053 --> 00:02:59,471
Am I the rude one here?

49
00:03:00,389 --> 00:03:01,973
Let's get out of here.

50
00:03:02,057 --> 00:03:04,559
You're the one
who needs to listen to me.

51
00:03:05,352 --> 00:03:06,353
What?

52
00:03:06,436 --> 00:03:08,939
Didn't your husband
spend a fortune recently?

53
00:03:09,690 --> 00:03:10,691
What was it on?

54
00:03:11,274 --> 00:03:12,401
A building?

55
00:03:14,820 --> 00:03:17,322
I see it.

56
00:03:18,990 --> 00:03:20,742
I see it. I can see it.

57
00:03:27,457 --> 00:03:28,458
Handcuffs.

58
00:03:28,834 --> 00:03:29,960
Prison uniform.

59
00:03:30,877 --> 00:03:32,003
Handcuffs?

60
00:03:33,338 --> 00:03:36,007
If you don't do anything,
your husband will go to prison.

61
00:03:39,594 --> 00:03:43,014
He's a man who doesn't need laws
to live the straight and narrow.

62
00:03:43,598 --> 00:03:44,808
Do you want to go with him?

63
00:03:46,101 --> 00:03:47,102
What?

64
00:03:47,185 --> 00:03:48,478
Unless you want to join him

65
00:03:49,563 --> 00:03:50,814
buy a paper talisman.

66
00:03:53,442 --> 00:03:55,694
- Let's go, Yi-gyeong.
- Your kid's not well.

67
00:03:57,654 --> 00:04:02,159
That's because you met and married
when you shouldn't have.

68
00:04:05,787 --> 00:04:07,330
Let's see...

69
00:04:14,546 --> 00:04:16,298
It's prayer beads
made from a meteorite.

70
00:04:16,923 --> 00:04:18,258
Keep this on you.

71
00:04:19,217 --> 00:04:21,052
Good things will happen to your child

72
00:04:21,887 --> 00:04:23,638
and your husband will be fine.

73
00:04:24,264 --> 00:04:25,265
Take them.

74
00:04:27,100 --> 00:04:28,101
Thanks.

75
00:04:29,519 --> 00:04:30,520
A million won.

76
00:04:31,772 --> 00:04:32,773
What?

77
00:04:32,856 --> 00:04:34,524
You got a huge discount
for being a first-timer.

78
00:04:37,903 --> 00:04:38,904
What?

79
00:04:42,157 --> 00:04:43,283
Do as I said.

80
00:04:45,160 --> 00:04:50,415
MAD CONCRETE DREAMS

81
00:04:52,459 --> 00:04:53,543
Mr. Gi?

82
00:04:53,835 --> 00:04:55,962
Hey, what are you doing?

83
00:04:56,463 --> 00:04:58,799
You aren't allowed to drink
at a convenience store these days.

84
00:04:58,882 --> 00:04:59,883
Is that so?

85
00:05:02,385 --> 00:05:04,304
I have something nice at my office.

86
00:05:04,930 --> 00:05:05,931
Come with me.

87
00:05:19,444 --> 00:05:23,281
M&amp;A REALTORS

88
00:05:25,492 --> 00:05:29,329
I bought this in Kyoto
to share with a special client.

89
00:05:32,958 --> 00:05:34,042
Here you go.

90
00:05:53,186 --> 00:05:55,397
Is something up, Hee-ju?

91
00:05:55,480 --> 00:05:56,898
Sorry.

92
00:05:56,982 --> 00:05:58,483
The alcohol got to me fast.

93
00:06:05,156 --> 00:06:06,575
My goodness.

94
00:06:14,958 --> 00:06:16,084
Mr. Gi.

95
00:06:17,294 --> 00:06:18,712
That Deputy Nam guy.

96
00:06:19,838 --> 00:06:21,381
Don't trust him too much.

97
00:06:22,173 --> 00:06:24,718
He's a psycho money-grabber.

98
00:06:25,302 --> 00:06:27,220
He'll do anything for money.

99
00:06:31,224 --> 00:06:32,225
Why say that?

100
00:06:35,812 --> 00:06:37,522
What is it? Is something wrong?

101
00:06:37,606 --> 00:06:39,441
You're just as bad.

102
00:06:39,524 --> 00:06:40,650
Why me?

103
00:06:42,736 --> 00:06:44,946
You said you'd cut me in.

104
00:06:45,780 --> 00:06:47,115
When we bought Hanmaeum Building.

105
00:06:47,198 --> 00:06:49,284
You said you'd give me a bonus.

106
00:06:49,367 --> 00:06:51,786
This is insane! It's 30 billion won!

107
00:06:51,870 --> 00:06:53,371
It's all thanks to you, Hee-ju.

108
00:06:53,455 --> 00:06:55,498
I'll get a bonus, right?

109
00:06:55,582 --> 00:06:57,125
Of course. Let's talk outside.

110
00:06:59,461 --> 00:07:01,796
Yes, right. I put it off too long.

111
00:07:02,255 --> 00:07:03,465
Let me see.

112
00:07:03,882 --> 00:07:05,508
I got your point.

113
00:07:05,592 --> 00:07:06,843
It was on my mind.

114
00:07:06,927 --> 00:07:07,928
Was it really?

115
00:07:08,261 --> 00:07:09,262
Here you go.

116
00:07:09,846 --> 00:07:11,473
Here are some gift certificates.

117
00:07:11,556 --> 00:07:13,350
They're valid at a lot of places

118
00:07:13,433 --> 00:07:14,893
so you'll have no problem using them.

119
00:07:15,226 --> 00:07:16,353
Are you serious?

120
00:07:19,606 --> 00:07:20,774
- Whatever.
- Okay.

121
00:07:20,857 --> 00:07:22,025
Let's clink glasses.

122
00:07:22,108 --> 00:07:23,151
- Yes.
- Here.

123
00:07:23,234 --> 00:07:24,819
- You should have some more.
- Gosh.

124
00:07:25,570 --> 00:07:26,947
We can slow down.

125
00:07:27,781 --> 00:07:29,532
- To the redevelopment.
- To the redevelopment.

126
00:07:29,616 --> 00:07:32,661
Let it be fun, constructive

127
00:07:32,744 --> 00:07:34,788
- and a blessing to others.
- Okay.

128
00:07:34,871 --> 00:07:38,124
M&amp;A REALTORS

129
00:07:43,254 --> 00:07:44,255
Hee-ju.

130
00:07:45,715 --> 00:07:47,008
Do you know about love?

131
00:07:52,055 --> 00:07:53,056
What's going on?

132
00:07:53,765 --> 00:07:55,684
Do you have trouble with your wife?

133
00:07:56,935 --> 00:07:57,936
No.

134
00:08:00,438 --> 00:08:01,481
What's the matter?

135
00:08:01,564 --> 00:08:03,400
You know I have a good hunch.

136
00:08:03,817 --> 00:08:05,819
It's pretty obvious something's up.

137
00:08:06,277 --> 00:08:07,278
No.

138
00:08:08,780 --> 00:08:09,781
Is it an affair?

139
00:08:13,743 --> 00:08:14,744
An affair?

140
00:08:17,038 --> 00:08:18,999
Affairs, affairs.

141
00:08:19,082 --> 00:08:21,501
A wind of affairs is blowing.

142
00:08:22,794 --> 00:08:23,795
A wind.

143
00:08:23,878 --> 00:08:25,880
I'm right. It's about an affair.

144
00:08:26,423 --> 00:08:27,424
Who with?

145
00:08:27,507 --> 00:08:29,718
Is it you or her? Who's cheating?

146
00:08:30,427 --> 00:08:31,428
Hee-ju.

147
00:08:32,887 --> 00:08:33,930
Listen.

148
00:08:34,180 --> 00:08:36,391
Legally speaking,
when you get divorced

149
00:08:37,017 --> 00:08:39,269
the one who had an affair
is the one at fault.

150
00:08:39,352 --> 00:08:42,480
That means the innocent one
is more advantageous

151
00:08:42,981 --> 00:08:44,315
when we divide the assets.

152
00:08:44,399 --> 00:08:45,650
I didn't have an affair

153
00:08:46,109 --> 00:08:48,528
but Seon did.

154
00:08:49,112 --> 00:08:50,739
Who with?

155
00:08:52,532 --> 00:08:54,034
I can't tell you that.

156
00:08:56,036 --> 00:08:57,454
Oh, no.

157
00:09:01,166 --> 00:09:02,417
I'm the one who got cheated on.

158
00:09:03,293 --> 00:09:05,503
Why do I feel so cornered?

159
00:09:06,004 --> 00:09:07,714
No, you're not.

160
00:09:07,797 --> 00:09:09,883
You're not boxed in a corner.

161
00:09:10,175 --> 00:09:12,802
You said you did nothing wrong.

162
00:09:13,428 --> 00:09:16,473
Sue your wife and demand a divorce.

163
00:09:16,556 --> 00:09:20,018
When it comes to splitting assets
or custody arrangements

164
00:09:20,101 --> 00:09:22,645
you will have an advantage
over your wife.

165
00:09:24,272 --> 00:09:26,691
You seem to see one side
and not the other.

166
00:09:29,986 --> 00:09:31,696
Love is an absolute power.

167
00:09:32,781 --> 00:09:35,200
It ranks way above the law.

168
00:09:36,868 --> 00:09:39,537
The one who loves the other more
is always at a disadvantage.

169
00:09:41,414 --> 00:09:42,415
You see

170
00:09:43,166 --> 00:09:45,251
I love my wife
more than she loves me.

171
00:09:45,960 --> 00:09:47,170
I'm an idiot.

172
00:09:47,253 --> 00:09:48,880
Poor you.

173
00:09:52,258 --> 00:09:53,259
Goodness.

174
00:09:55,220 --> 00:09:57,472
It must be so hard on you.

175
00:09:57,555 --> 00:10:01,935
- An affair...
- Oh, dear.

176
00:10:02,018 --> 00:10:04,604
A wind of affairs...

177
00:10:06,106 --> 00:10:09,192
- A gust of wind...
- An affair...

178
00:10:11,736 --> 00:10:12,737
An affair...

179
00:10:38,888 --> 00:10:40,223
The photo came out nicely.

180
00:10:45,019 --> 00:10:47,021
I wish to expose
Pyeongbukgwan heiress

181
00:10:47,105 --> 00:10:49,107
Jeon Yi-gyeong's violent streak.

182
00:10:53,903 --> 00:10:54,904
Mr. Gi.

183
00:10:58,992 --> 00:11:00,910
- Mr. Gi.
- Yes?

184
00:11:20,013 --> 00:11:21,139
Mr. Gi.

185
00:11:25,852 --> 00:11:29,230
MR. MIN HWAL-SUNG

186
00:11:31,608 --> 00:11:34,110
Mr. Min, I've got something big.

187
00:11:34,194 --> 00:11:35,737
Would you like to strike a deal?

188
00:11:39,908 --> 00:11:41,326
We've been married for ten years.

189
00:11:41,701 --> 00:11:45,246
I was a victim of vicious
physical and verbal abuse

190
00:11:45,330 --> 00:11:47,415
