191
00:11:47,498 --> 00:11:48,499
HEE-JU

192
00:11:53,046 --> 00:11:54,047
What's this?

193
00:11:54,672 --> 00:11:58,051
MR. MIN, I'VE GOT SOMETHING BIG

194
00:11:58,134 --> 00:12:01,471
WOULD YOU LIKE TO STRIKE A DEAL?

195
00:12:01,804 --> 00:12:04,224
She only texts
when she needs something.

196
00:12:07,310 --> 00:12:08,311
What's he doing?

197
00:12:15,526 --> 00:12:16,527
Hee-ju.

198
00:12:17,946 --> 00:12:19,072
Do you know about love?

199
00:12:20,907 --> 00:12:21,908
What's going on?

200
00:12:22,617 --> 00:12:24,535
Do you have trouble with your wife?

201
00:12:25,870 --> 00:12:31,709
M&amp;A REALTORS

202
00:12:31,793 --> 00:12:35,964
M&amp;A REALTORS

203
00:12:54,023 --> 00:12:56,109
It's pretty obvious something's up.

204
00:12:56,901 --> 00:12:59,821
A wind of affairs...

205
00:13:00,738 --> 00:13:03,658
- A gust of wind...
- An affair...

206
00:13:12,500 --> 00:13:13,543
Hee-ju.

207
00:13:24,512 --> 00:13:25,513
Hee-ju.

208
00:13:26,597 --> 00:13:27,598
Hee-ju.

209
00:13:34,230 --> 00:13:35,231
Hee-ju.

210
00:13:36,065 --> 00:13:37,692
Man, what time is it?

211
00:13:40,987 --> 00:13:41,988
Hee-ju.

212
00:13:42,989 --> 00:13:44,115
Get up.

213
00:13:45,366 --> 00:13:46,367
Hee-ju.

214
00:14:08,389 --> 00:14:09,474
Get in.

215
00:14:27,617 --> 00:14:29,452
Why are you giving me that look?
It's uncomfortable.

216
00:14:30,453 --> 00:14:31,996
I liked you from the very start.

217
00:14:32,830 --> 00:14:33,831
You what?

218
00:14:36,876 --> 00:14:40,213
I had a crush on you since the moment
Su-jong introduced us.

219
00:14:41,047 --> 00:14:43,549
You don't know how much I wished
you two would break up.

220
00:14:43,800 --> 00:14:45,301
Stop it.

221
00:14:46,552 --> 00:14:48,137
What we did was a mistake.

222
00:14:48,513 --> 00:14:50,598
Before you two got married

223
00:14:50,932 --> 00:14:52,683
if I'd told you how I felt

224
00:14:54,352 --> 00:14:55,770
would we have gotten married?

225
00:14:56,604 --> 00:14:57,605
I'm going home.

226
00:14:59,690 --> 00:15:01,859
Legally speaking,
when you get divorced

227
00:15:01,943 --> 00:15:04,153
the one who had an affair
is the one at fault.

228
00:15:04,237 --> 00:15:06,322
That means the innocent one

229
00:15:06,406 --> 00:15:07,740
- is more advantageous
- What is this?

230
00:15:07,824 --> 00:15:08,991
when we divide the assets.

231
00:15:09,075 --> 00:15:10,910
Su-jong is getting ready
to divorce you.

232
00:15:10,993 --> 00:15:13,246
But Seon did.

233
00:15:13,329 --> 00:15:14,330
What?

234
00:15:14,414 --> 00:15:16,374
You're about to be backstabbed.

235
00:15:16,457 --> 00:15:17,542
I can't tell you that.

236
00:15:19,752 --> 00:15:21,129
Oh, no.

237
00:15:21,212 --> 00:15:23,714
Isn't this Hee-ju the realtor?

238
00:15:27,051 --> 00:15:28,594
You could get walked all over.

239
00:15:29,595 --> 00:15:30,930
Prepare yourself to divorce him.

240
00:15:32,473 --> 00:15:34,475
